<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=5 WIDTH=90%><TR><TD></TD><TD><CENTER><H1>   
Chapter 2</H1></CENTER></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V1><H4>1</H4></TD>  
<TD><P>Then Jonah prayed unto YHVH his ELOHIYM out of the fish's belly,</P></TD>
</TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V2><H4>2</H4></TD><TD><P>And said, I cried by   
reason of mine affliction unto YHVH, and he heard me; out of the belly of hell  
cried I, and thou heardest my voice.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V3>
<H4>3</H4></TD><TD><P>For thou hadst cast me into the deep, in the midst of the 
seas; and the floods compassed me about: all thy billows and thy waves passed   
over me.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V4><H4>4</H4></TD><TD><P>Then  
I said, I am cast out of thy sight; yet I will look again toward thy holy       
temple.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V5><H4>5</H4></TD><TD><P>The    
waters compassed me about, even to the soul: the depth closed me round about,   
the weeds were wrapped about my head.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A        
NAME=V6><H4>6</H4></TD><TD><P>I went down to the bottoms of the mountains; the  
earth with her bars was about me for ever: yet hast thou brought up my life     
from corruption, O YHVH my ELOHIYM.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V7> 
<H4>7</H4></TD><TD><P>When my soul fainted within me I remembered YHVH: and my  
prayer came in unto thee, into thine holy temple.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD          
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V8><H4>8</H4></TD><TD><P>They that observe lying vanities    
forsake their own mercy.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V9><H4>9</H4>  
</TD><TD><P>But I will sacrifice unto thee with the voice of thanksgiving; I    
will pay that that I have vowed. Salvation is of YHVH.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD     
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V10><H4>10</H4></TD><TD><P>And YHVH spake unto the fish, and 
it vomited out Jonah upon the dry land.</P></TD></TR></TABLE><!--This Software  
